data.title: Vintage oversize photograph of Patti D'Arbanville, circa 1970s by Patti D'Arbanville (subject); Anthony Rios (photographer): (1970)
data.meta_description: Europa Photos, London - 1970 - Vintage borderless oversize photograph of actress and model Patti D'Arbanville in London. Partial stamp of photographer Anthony Rios on the verso, along with the stamp of Europa Photos. D'Arbanville was cast by Andy Warhol in her first feature film at the age of 16, in the 1968 film "Flesh." She went on to appear in a number of risqu√© roles throughout the 1970s and 1980s, including Andy Warhol's "L'Amour" in 1973 and David Hamilton's "Bilitis" in 1977. 11.25 x 8.5 inches. Brief wear at the corners, else Near Fine. - Vintage oversize photograph of Patti D'Arbanville, circa 1970s
